                    loops for configuration errors, program doesn't exit if
                    a configuration error has been found).

                  - Fixed some problems with the creation of toolbars when the
                    configuration file misses some needed keywords.
                  
                  - Loading a configuration file twice is now prevented.
                    This also avoids the recursive configuration file
                    loading problem.
                  
                  - FIX: Arexx command are now really case insensitive.
                  
                  - FIX: No more problems if a configuration file does not
                    exist or cannot be read.
                  

  29.10.98 v3.4   - Window iconification.
                  - New ICONIFY Arexx command with different parameteers.
                  - Code optimization that decreses memory usage a bit and
                    makes the new binary only 280 bytes bigger than the
                    previous release.


  (01.02.99) v3.5 - Completely bug fixed and highly optimized.
                  - Only for personal use.
  
  (27.07.99) v3.6 - Probably last public release.
                  - Removed Project Manager.
                  - FIX: AREXX comands now answer back (BAH can be closed
                    directly from BED).
                  - FIX: Problem creating lines with TEXT and SPACE only
                    gadgets.
                  - Centered,left and right aligned text labels added
                  - The window position can now be saved and restored
